column15:
Note:  All the drawings of  the Atlantic site Upper Chamber Floor Slab show the nomenclature "SF" despite the fact that the RFC of the Floor Slabs of the Middle  and Lower Chamber of the Atlantic site, as well as the RFC of the Floor Slab of Upper, Middle and Lower Chamber of the Pacific site all show the nomenclature "FS".  

Moreover, the file "Summary Design of Lifts and Pours", produced by the Contractor also has the nomenclature "FS" for all the floor slabs of both sites.

For othat reason, this .xlsx file keeps the nomenclature "FS" instead of the "SF" showed in the RFC drawings.
